- Mobile Photo Editor
    - status: POC | mode: Claude Code | updated: 2026-04-01
    - A standalone Android photo editor with Telegram-style editing capabilities
    - License: GPL v2 (algorithms derived from Telegram)

- Features
    - Photo adjustments (OpenGL ES 2.0):
        - Exposure, Contrast, Saturation, Warmth
        - Highlights, Shadows, Sharpen, Fade
        - Grain, Vignette
    - Crop and rotate:
        - Freeform, 1:1, 4:3, 3:4, 16:9, 9:16 aspect ratios
        - Free rotation (-45 to +45 degrees) with rotation wheel
        - 90-degree rotation and mirror
        - Pan and pinch-to-zoom
    - Drawing:
        - Freehand brush with 8 color options
        - Adjustable brush size
        - Eraser tool
        - Undo support (up to 20 steps)

- Architecture
    - Two modules:
        - app/: Thin shell with photo picker and permissions
        - editor/: Photo editor library module
    - Filter pipeline:
        - OpenGL ES 2.0 with GLSL shaders ported from Telegram
        - Multi-pass rendering: sharpen, tools (all adjustments), display
        - Real-time preview on TextureView
    - Crop:
        - CropAreaView (overlay with draggable handles)
        - CropView (image display with pan/zoom)
        - CropRotationWheel (fine rotation control)
    - Paint:
        - Canvas-based stamp rendering
        - Undo via bitmap snapshots

- Building
    - Requirements:
        - Android SDK (platform 35, build tools 36.1.0)
        - JDK 8+
    - Build:
        - ./gradlew assembleDebug
    - Output:
        - app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk

